%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanging%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%20likely%20won't%20be%20getting%20as%20big%20of%20a%20wage%20bump%20as%20past%20job%20switchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you'd%20have%20done%20the%20same%20thing%20a%20year%20ago%20or%2018%20months%20ago%2C%20you'd%20have%20probably%20got%20double%20the%20pay%20rise%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Tinsley%2C%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstitute.bankofamerica.com%2Feconomic-insights%2Fthe-great-hesitation-labor-market.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20the%20median%20pay%20gain%20for%20those%20switching%20jobs%20was%20around%2020%25%20during%20the%20Great%20Resignation%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20based%20on%20the%20bank's%20internal%20data.%20However%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bmedian%20pay%20raises%20appear%20to%20have%20moderated%20to%20around%2010%25%26quot%3B%20as%20of%20this%20past%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FG749f%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22As%20of%20May%2C%20median%20pay%20raises%20for%20J2J%20movers%20moderated%5Cnto%2010%25%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20still%20moving%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20pay%20rises%20they're%20getting%20are%20below%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20Tinsley%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20seems%20to%20suggest%20there's%20been%20a%20sort%20of%20supply%20shift.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20desire%20to%20move%20jobs%20might%20be%20outpacing%20the%20demand%20from%20firms%20to%20take%20people%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlantafed.org%2Fchcs%2Fwage-growth-tracker%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAtlanta%20Fed's%20Wage%20Growth%20Tracker%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20shown%20pay%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egrowth%20cooling%20for%20job%20switchers%20since%20the%20highs%20seen%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20based%20on%20the%20three-month%20moving%20average%20of%20median%20wage%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20data%20out%20Friday%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fces%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20wage%20growth%20for%20private%20employees%20generally%20has%20moderated%20slightly.%20Average%20hourly%20earnings%20rose%20by%203.9%25%20from%20June%202023%20to%20June%202024%2C%20following%20a%20year-over-year%20increase%20of%204.1%25%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drops%20in%20the%20median%20pay%20raise%20for%20job-to-job%20movers%20from%202022%20to%202024%20were%20felt%20across%20workers%20in%20all%20income%20groups%2C%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20found.%20Still%2C%20the%20report%20noted%20that%20lower-income%20Bank%20of%20America%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20those%20making%20under%20%2450%2C000%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20had%20the%20highest%20median%20pay%20gains.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20medians%20for%20middle-%20and%20higher-income%20job%20changers%20aren't%20even%20in%20the%20double%20digits%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FftSdN%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20pay%20growth%20for%20J2J%20movers%20for%20higher-%20and%5Cnmiddle-income%20customers%20is%20below%202019%20levels%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22513%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20those%20middle-%20and%20upper-income%20job%20seekers%20may%20%26quot%3Bhave%20somewhat%20less%20leverage%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-job-salary-resesarch-bonus-compensation-negotiation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebargaining%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20negotiating%20a%20raise%20on%20taking%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETinsley%20linked%20that%20drop%20to%20turbulence%20in%20some%20particularly%20high-paying%20sectors.%20%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20there%20was%20a%20shakeout%20of%20jobs%20in%20tech%20and%20to%20some%20extent%20in%20finance%20last%20year%2C%20and%20I%20guess%20that%20has%20probably%20backed%20a%20little%20of%20the%20bargaining%20power%20out%20of%20those%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Tinsley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20shows%20that%20job-hopping%20might%20be%20slowing%20down.%20New%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fjlt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20Tuesday%20also%20showed%20that%20the%20quits%20rate%20has%20consistently%20been%202.2%25%20for%20seven%20months%2C%20and%20the%20quits%20level%20was%20around%203.5%20million%20in%20May%2C%20far%20below%20its%20Great%20Resignation%20high%20of%204.5%20million%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Tinsley%20said%20there%20still%20is%20a%20reasonable%20rate%20of%20job-to-job%20changes%20happening%20even%20with%20the%20pullback%20in%20raises.%20He%20said%20there's%20a%20risk%20and%20a%20reward%20when%20people%20change%20jobs.%20The%20risk%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20could%20be%20the%20track%20record%20you%20have%20to%20build%20up%20at%20your%20latest%20workplace%2C%20while%20the%20reward%20could%20be%20related%20to%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job-changing%20data%20implies%20there%20are%20still%20some%20optimistic%20job%20searchers%20in%20the%20still-strong%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-june-econ