C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20New%20York%20City%20Airbnb%20host%20was%20shut%20down%20under%20the%20short-term%20rental%20law.%20He's%20now%20renting%20his%20basement%20illegally%20on%20Facebook%20and%20making%20crucial%20income%20after%20he%20was%20laid%20off.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Row%20houses%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668440ec268f62ba18a6d018%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERow%20houses%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York.%3Cp%3ELindsey%20Nicholson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20New%20Yorker's%20Airbnb%20business%20thrived%20until%20a%20new%20city%20law%20shut%20it%20down.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENYC%20moved%20to%20restrict%20short-term%20rentals%2C%20in%20part%20to%20address%20the%20city's%20housing%20shortage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20former%20host%20now%20rents%20his%20basement%20through%20Facebook%20and%20friends%2C%20earning%20income%20after%20a%20layoff.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Paul%20and%20his%20wife%20bought%20their%20townhouse%20in%20Astoria%2C%20Queens%2C%20in%202013%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20transform%20their%20basement%20into%20a%20guest%20suite%20for%20visiting%20family%20and%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20pay%20off%20the%20loan%20they%20took%20out%20for%20the%20renovation%2C%20the%20couple%20rented%20their%20basement%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20a%20bedroom%2C%20living%20space%2C%20and%20a%20kitchenette%20%E2%80%94%20on%20Airbnb%20for%20short-term%20stays%20in%20between%20family%20visits.%20They%20were%20quickly%20inundated%20with%20eager%20guests.%20There%20aren't%20many%20hotels%20in%20Astoria%20%E2%80%94%20a%20largely%20residential%20neighborhood%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20few%20that%20exist%20are%20%26quot%3Bdinky%26quot%3B%20and%20expensive%2C%20Paul%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20several%20years%20and%20the%20couple%20is%20still%20renting%20out%20the%20basement%20for%20short%20periods.%20But%20they're%20knowingly%20violating%20New%20York%20City's%20new%20law%20banning%20most%20short-term%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20Airbnb%2C%20they%20hosted%20tourists%20from%20across%20Asia%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20the%20US%2C%20as%20well%20as%20people%20visiting%20family%20members%20in%20Queens.%20Guests%20usually%20stayed%20about%20three%20or%20four%20days%2C%20but%20sometimes%20as%20long%20as%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20enormously%20profitable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Paul%2C%20whose%20name%20was%20changed%20for%20this%20story%20to%20protect%20his%20family's%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20high%20season%2C%20he%20said%20they%20charged%20up%20to%20%24300%20a%20night%20for%20the%20space%2C%20which%20can%20comfortably%20sleep%20four%2C%20and%20they%20never%20charged%20less%20than%20%24150%20a%20night.%20In%20a%20good%20month%2C%20it%20brought%20in%20nearly%20%243%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20their%20Airbnb%20earnings%20report.%20But%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20in%20early%202020%2C%20they%20were%20forced%20to%20shut%20down%20their%20Airbnb%20business.%20Because%20the%20basement%20doesn't%20have%20a%20proper%20kitchen%2C%20including%20an%20oven%2C%20they%20couldn't%20rent%20it%20out%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20years%20later%2C%20they%20were%20just%20about%20to%20re-list%20their%20basement%20on%20Airbnb%20when%20the%20New%20York%20City%20government%20passed%20new%20regulations%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fsite%2Fspecialenforcement%2Fregistration-law%2Fregistration.page%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELocal%20Law%2018%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20cracking%20down%20on%20short-term%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20law%2C%20homeowners%20can%20host%20paying%20guests%20for%20less%20than%2030%20days%20only%20if%20their%20unit%20is%20in%20an%20approved%20building%2C%20they%20rent%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20two%20guests%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20they%20stay%20in%20the%20home%20with%20their%20guests.%20The%20law%20also%20requires%20that%20guests%20have%20access%20to%20the%20entire%20unit%20and%20that%20there%20aren't%20any%20locked%20doors%20inside%20the%20home.%20Every%20potential%20host%20has%20to%20apply%20and%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20city's%20Office%20of%20Special%20Enforcement%20(OSE).%20Hosts%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fassets%2Fspecialenforcement%2Fdownloads%2Fpdfs%2FFINAL-RULES-GOVERNING-REGISTRATION-AND-REQUIREMENTS-FOR-SHORT-TERM-RENTALS.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efined%20up%20to%20%245%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20repeated%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20and%20his%20wife%20applied%2C%20but%20they%20were%20denied%2C%20according%20to%20documentation%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20To%20comply%20with%20the%20law%2C%20they%20would%20need%20to%20open%20up%20their%20personal%20living%20room%20and%20kitchen%20to%20their%20Airbnb%20guests.%20An%20OSE%20representative%20helpfully%20explained%20how%20they%20could%20alter%20their%20home%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20law%2C%20but%20Paul%20and%20his%20wife%20felt%20the%20changes%20would%20%26quot%3Bsacrifice%20our%20own%20sense%20of%20privacy%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20they%20gave%20up%20on%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20city%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-airbnb-crackdown-squeezes-hosts-and-renters-starting-september-5-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegan%20enforcing%20LL18%20last%20September%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-numbers-shrink-hotel-prices-soar-ban-nyc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20short-term%20rental%20listings%20has%20plummeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Airbnb%20listings%20for%20stays%20of%20less%20than%2030%20days%20fell%20from%2022%2C246%20in%20August%20of%20last%20year%2C%20just%20before%20the%20city%20began%20enforcing%20the%20law%2C%20to%20nearly%204%2C000%20in%20May%202024%2C%20a%20roughly%2082%25%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20June%2024%2C%20the%20city%20had%20received%206%2C395%20applications%20for%20short-term%20rentals%2C%20according%20to%20OSE.%20The%20office%20has%20approved%202%2C276%20of%20these%2C%20denied%201%2C746%2C%20and%20asked%202%2C269%20applicants%20to%20submit%20additional%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELL18%20aims%20to%20address%20the%20city's%20severe%20housing%20shortage%20by%20opening%20homes%20to%20long-term%20renters%20that%20were%20previously%20reserved%20for%20visitors.%20Some%20evidence%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-ban-makes-rents-housing-prices-drop-irvine-california-study-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20from%20Irvine%2C%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20suggests%20that%20restricting%20short-term%20rentals%20can%20reduce%20rents.%20Less%20than%20a%20year%20into%20enforcement%20of%20the%20near-ban%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20New%20York%20City%20is%20achieving%20this%20goal%2C%20but%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-numbers-shrink-hotel-prices-soar-ban-nyc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20made%20hotel%20rooms%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2251eb259b-67a7-460a-9bd2-d5d42114e214%5C%22%3ECrucial%20income%20after%20a%20layoff%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20city%20rejected%20his%20application%2C%20Paul%20says%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bpissed%20off%26quot%3B%20and%20decided%20to%20find%20other%20ways%20to%20rent%20the%20basement%20out%20to%20short-term%20guests.%20So%20he%20began%20promoting%20it%20in%20various%20Facebook%20groups%20and%20through%20friends%20in%20the%20neighborhood.%20He%20quickly%20found%20takers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20many%20former%20Airbnbs%20gone%20and%20hotel%20rates%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20business%20has%20been%20good.%20For%20the%20last%20about%2018%20months%2C%20he's%20managed%20to%20regularly%20rent%20the%20place%20out%20for%20short-term%20and%20medium-term%20stays%2C%20charging%20between%20%24150%20and%20%24200%20per%20night%20or%20%242%2C500%20for%20a%20month-long%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20particularly%20worried%20about%20being%20fined%20by%20the%20city%20because%20he%20thinks%20the%20government%20is%20more%20concerned%20with%20shutting%20down%20large-scale%2C%20short-term%20rental%20businesses%20rather%20than%20small-time%20property%20owners.%20OSE%20told%20BI%20it's%20working%20with%20Airbnb%20and%20other%20short-term%20rental%20companies%20to%20ensure%20they're%20in%20compliance%20before%20it%20begins%20fining%20hosts%20who%20violate%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20Paul%20is%20hosting%20a%20local%20family%20waiting%20for%20renovations%20to%20be%20finished%20on%20their%20new%20home%20in%20the%20neighborhood.%20And%20they%20have%20lots%20of%20regular%2C%20repeat%20guests%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20grandparents%20visiting%20from%20out%20of%20town%20and%20others%20who%20want%20to%20stay%20near%20family%20who%20live%20in%20Astoria.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20a%20place%20that's%20within%20walking%20distance%20and%20also%20has%20the%20amenities%20of%20a%20home%20that%20you%20won't%20find%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20that%20Airbnb%20and%20other%20short-term%20rentals%20in%20New%20York%20City%20should%20be%20regulated%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20think%20LL18%20does%20enough%20to%20protect%20small-time%20hosts%20like%20himself%2C%20who%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20rent%20out%20their%20space%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20agree%20with%20the%20sentiment%20behind%20the%20regulations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20that%20the%20regulations%20were%20designed%20as%20sort%20of%20blunt%20instruments%20rather%20than%20a%20precision%20tool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Paul%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20his%20job%20as%20a%20TV%20producer%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20the%20family%20has%20come%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20income%20from%20short-term%20renting.%20He%20also%20feels%20they're%20doing%20a%20service%20for%20visitors%20who%20need%20a%20more%20affordable%20place%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20best%20use%20of%20that%20space%20I%20could%20think%20of%20is%20to%20rent%20it%20out%20to%20local%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20we%20use%20this%20space%20is%20good%20for%20Astoria%2C%20and%20it's%20good%20for%20New%20York%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20living%20here%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20been%20impacted%20by%20New%20York%20City's%20short-term%20rental%20regulations%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aerelman%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eerelman%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-ban-nyc-host-rents-illegally-short-term-facebook-queens-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720344723000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668440ec268f62ba18a6d018%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-ban-nyc-host-rents-illegally-short-term-facebook-queens-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20couple%20in%20Astoria%2C%20Queens%2C%20rented%20out%20their%20basement%20on%20Airbnb%20for%20years.%20New%20city%20regulations%20have%20made%20that%20illegal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-ban-nyc-host-rents-illegally-short-term-facebook-queens-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Slain%20Mayawati