%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECo-sleeping%20won't%20be%20a%20lifelong%20arrangement%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20it%20works%20for%20us.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20just%208%20months%20old%2C%20our%20oldest%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-co-sleeps-with-daughters-southern-parenting-viral-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleeping%20in%20our%20bed%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20night.%20(Before%20that%2C%20he%20slept%20in%20his%20yet-to-be-recalled%20Rock%20'n%20Play.)%20It%20was%20something%20we%20said%20we'd%20never%20do.%20We%20weren't%20going%20to%20be%20co-sleepers.%20But%20suddenly%2C%20we%20had%20a%20son%20who%20refused%20to%20sleep%20in%20his%20crib%2C%20and%20we%20were%20tired%20and%20a%20couple%20of%20softies.%20In%20our%20king-sized%20bed%2C%20there%20was%20plenty%20of%20room%2C%20and%20he%20began%20going%20to%20bed%20with%20us%20regularly..%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20we%20had%20another%20son.%20This%20one%20liked%20his%20crib.%20He%20slept%20in%20it%20until%20he%20was%203.%20By%20then%2C%20our%20oldest%20was%205%20and%20slept%20in%20his%20own%20bed%20about%20half%20the%20time.%20It%20was%20only%20when%20our%20youngest%20wandered%20in%20and%20saw%20his%20brother%20in%20our%20bed%20that%20he%20even%20realized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-co-slept-children-travel-showed-many-cultures-share-beds-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eco-sleeping%20was%20an%20option%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20like%20a%20lightbulb%20moment%20for%20him.%20But%20this%20caused%20a%20problem%3A%20while%20one%20baby%20fit%20fine%2C%20two%20growing%20boys%20don't%20fit%20quite%20so%20comfortably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-sleeping-parents-and-kids-ok-until-child-is-prepubescent-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eco-sleeping%20not%20a%20lifelong%20scenario%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20our%20kids%20won't%20always%20want%20to%20sleep%20with%20us%20%E2%80%94%20so%20for%20now%2C%20it's%20comfort%20that%20we%20can%20provide%20them.%20The%20warmth%20and%20safety%20of%20%26quot%3BMommy%20and%20Daddy's%20bed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20only%20one%20exception%20to%20co-sleeping%3A%20cases%20of%20the%20stomach%20flu%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20share%20the%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bethaney%20Phillips'%20two%20kids%20sleeping%20in%20her%20oldest%20son's%20bed%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668571bb268f62ba18a72f11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBethaney%20Phillips'%20two%20kids%20co-sleep%20with%20her%20and%20her%20husband.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Bethaney%20Phillips%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f54ae8f7-fc98-4ced-861e-eaa3428b4bab%5C%22%3EThey%20usually%20start%20the%20night%20in%20their%20own%20bed%2C%20but%20almost%20always%20end%20up%20in%20ours%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boys%20climb%20into%20their%20own%20twin-sized%20beds%20and%20get%20cuddles.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdefault-parent-hard-spend-time-kids-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoth%20want%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20infuriating%20compliment%20%E2%80%94%20so%20I%20take%20turns%20about%20who%20gets%20snuggles%20first.%20After%20a%20long%20day%2C%20snuggler%20number%20two%20is%20likely%20asleep%20before%20I%20reach%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%20in%20the%20night%2C%20one%20or%20both%20of%20them%20crawls%20into%20our%20bed.%20It%20might%20have%20been%20a%20bad%20dream%2C%20they%20may%20have%20been%20cold%2C%20or%20they%20could%20have%20just%20woken%20and%20wanted%20some%20cuddling%20time.%20It's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20me%20to%20wake%20up%20to%20find%20a%20child%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20me%20and%20my%20husband%2C%20or%20wedging%20%3Cem%3Eme%3C%2Fem%3E%20into%20the%20middle.%20It's%20also%20not%20uncommon%20for%20me%20to%20move%20and%20relocate%20to%20their%20bed%2C%20which%20is%20plenty%20comfortable.%20And%20a%205'3%26quot%3B%2C%20I'm%20an%20easy%20fit.%20(My%206'1%26quot%3B%20husband%20hangs%20his%20feet%20off%20the%20end.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20days%20when%20the%20kids%20are%20overly%20tired%20or%20upset%2C%20we%20allow%20them%20to%20go%20to%20bed%20in%20ours%20and%20then%20move%20them%20once%20they%20are%20in%20a%20deep%20sleep.%20Occasionally%2C%20this%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20reward%2C%20too.%20Of%20course%2C%20they%20ask%20not%20to%20be%20moved%2C%20to%20sleep%20there%20all%20night%2C%20but%20we%20make%20no%20such%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22403%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bethaney%20Phillips'%20younger%20son%20tucked%20into%20bed.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668572961f0c1cd6d7314372%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22303%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBethaney%20Phillips%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20been%20co-sleeping%20with%20their%20kids%20for%20years.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Bethaney%20Phillips%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acb21a19-8e49-4570-b36c-e81c47d64475%5C%22%3EWe%20don't%20see%20things%20changing%20anytime%20soon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20jokes%20that%20we%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-divorce-same-room-separate-beds-relationship-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20mattress%20in%20our%20room%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20essentially%20doubling%20the%20size%20of%20our%20current%20bed.%20And%20while%20I%20know%20our%20habits%20are%20a%20bit%20unorthodox%2C%20it%20also%20allows%20us%20the%20freedom%20to%20sleep%20in%20the%20way%20everyone%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20each%20have%20night%20lights%20in%20their%20rooms%2C%20and%20we%20run%20two%20fans%20on%20high.%20The%20youngest%20piles%20his%20bed%20with%20about%2015%20stuffies%2C%20while%20hard%20toys%20such%20as%20