d-the-ten-commandments-discovered-in-austria-chapel%2Farticleshow%2F111547963.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2F1500-year-old-relic-linked-to-moses-and-the-ten-commandments-discovered-in-austria-chapel%2Famp_articleshow%2F111547963.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2F1500-year-old-relic-linked-to-moses-and-the-ten-commandments-discovered-in-austria-chapel%2Famp_articleshow%2F111547963.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Bhole%20Baba%20forcibly%20occupied%20land%20for%20ashram%20in%20Rajasthan'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720323377000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111548283%2Cimgsize-80284.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fjaipur%2Fbhole-baba-forcibly-occupied-land-for-ashram-plot-seller%2Farticleshow%2F111548277.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alwar%20village's%20ashram%2C%20linked%20to%20Baba%20Surajpal%20Jatav%2C%20faces%20accusations%20of%20land%20dispute%20and%20restricted%20access.%20Following%20a%20tragic%20stampede%20in%20Hathras%2C%20demands%20for%20the%20Baba's%20arrest%20arise.%20The%20village%20of%20Sahajpura%20seeks%20justice%20and%20answers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fjaipur%2Fbhole-baba-forcibly-occupied-land-for-ashram-plot-seller%2Farticleshow%2F111548277.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20Confirm%20Earth's%20Core%20Has%20Slowed%2C%20Now%20Moving%20In%20Reverse%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDeep%20within%20Earth%20lies%20a%20solid%20metal%20ball%20that%20rotates%20independently%20of%20our%20spinning%20planet%2C%20like%20a%20top%20whirling%20inside%20a%20larger%20top%2C%20enveloped%20in%20mystery.%20Since%20its%20discovery%20by%20Danish%20seismologist%20Inge%20Lehmann%20in%201936%2C%20this%20inner%20core%20has%20fascinated%20researchers.%20Its%20movement%20-%20including%20rotation%20speed%20and%20direction%20-%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20decades-long%20debate.%20Increasing%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20the%20core's%20spin%20has%20changed%20significantly%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%20scientists%20remain%20divided%20on%20what%20exactly%20is%20happening%20and%20what%20it%20signifies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20challenge%20is%20that%20Earth's%20deep%20interior%20is%20impossible%20to%20observe%20or%20sample%20directly.%20Seismologists%20have%20gathered%20information%20about%20the%20inner%20core's%20motion%20by%20examining%20the%20behaviour%20of%20waves%20from%20large%20earthquakes%20that%20reach%20this%20area.%20Differences%20between%20waves%20of%20similar%20strengths%20that%20passed%20through%20the%20core%20at%20different%20times%20have%20allowed%20scientists%20to%20measure%20changes%20in%20the%20inner%20core's%20position%20and%20calculate%20its%20spin%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F07%2F05%2Fscience%2Fearth-inner-core-rotation-slowdown-cycle-scn%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDifferential%20rotation%20of%20the%20inner%20core%20was%20proposed%20as%20a%20phenomenon%20in%20the%201970s%20and%20'80s%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20the%20'90s%20that%20seismological%20evidence%20was%20published%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Lauren%20Waszek%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20of%20physical%20sciences%20at%20James%20Cook%20University%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20debated%20how%20to%20interpret%20these%20findings.%20%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20of%20making%20detailed%20observations%20of%20the%20inner%20core%2C%20due%20to%20its%20remoteness%20and%20limited%20available%20data%2C%20is%20the%20primary%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Waszek.%20Consequently%2C%20%26quot%3Bstudies%20in%20subsequent%20years%20and%20decades%20have%20disagreed%20on%20the%20rate%20and%20direction%20of%20the%20inner%20core's%20rotation%20relative%20to%20the%20mantle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20Some%20analyses%20even%20suggested%20that%20the%20core%20didn't%20rotate%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20promising%20model%20proposed%20in%202023%20described%20an%20inner%20core%20that%20had%20previously%20spun%20faster%20than%20Earth%20itself%20but%20was%20now%20spinning%20slower.%20For%20a%20period%2C%20the%20core's%20rotation%20matched%20Earth's%20spin.%20Then%2C%20it%20slowed%20even%20further%2C%20eventually%20moving%20backwards%20relative%20to%20the%20fluid%20layers%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20some%20experts%20cautioned%20that%20more%20data%20was%20needed%20to%20support%20this%20conclusion.%20Now%2C%20another%20team%20of%20scientists%20has%20provided%20compelling%20new%20evidence%20for%20this%20hypothesis.%20Research%20published%20on%20June%2012%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%20not%20only%20confirms%20the%20core's%20slowdown%20but%20also%20supports%20the%202023%20proposal%20that%20this%20deceleration%20is%20part%20of%20a%20decades-long%20pattern%20of%20speed%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20findings%20also%20confirm%20that%20the%20changes%20in%20rotational%20speed%20follow%20a%2070-year%20cycle%2C%20said%20study%20co-author%20Dr%20John%20Vidale%2C%20Dean's%20Professor%20of%20Earth%20Sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California's%20Dornsife%20College%20of%20Letters%2C%20Arts%20and%20Sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20arguing%20about%20this%20for%2020%20years%2C%20and%20I%20think%20this%20nails%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Vidale%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we've%20ended%20the%20debate%20on%20whether%20the%20inner%20core%20moves%20and%20what's%20been%20its%20pattern%20for%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20decades.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20everyone%20is%20convinced%20the%20matter%20is%20settled.%20The%20implications%20of%20the%20inner%20core's%20slowdown%20for%20our%20planet%20remain%20an%20open%20question%2C%20with%20some%20experts%20suggesting%20that%20Earth's%20magnetic%20field%20could%20be%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuried%20about%203%2C220%20miles%20(5%2C180%20kilometres)%20deep%20inside%20Earth%2C%20the%20solid%20metal%20inner%20core%20is%20surrounded%20by%20a%20liquid%20metal%20outer%20core.%20Composed%20mostly%20of%20iron%20and%20nickel%2C%20the%20inner%20core%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20as%20hot%20as%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20sun%20-%20about%209%2C800%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20(5%2C400%20degrees%20Celsius).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarth's%20magnetic%20field%20pulls%20on%20this%20solid%20ball%20of%20hot%20metal%2C%20causing%20it%20to%20spin.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20gravity%20and%20flow%20of%20the%20fluid%20outer%20core%20and%20mantle%20exert%20a%20drag%20on%20the%20core.%20Over%20many%20decades%2C%20the%20push%20and%20pull%20of%20these%20forces%20have%20resulted%20in%20variations%20in%20the%20core's%20rotational%20speed%2C%20according%20to%20Vidale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20movement%20of%20metal-rich%20fluid%20in%20the%20outer%20core%20generates%20electrical%20currents%20that%20power%20Earth's%20magnetic%20field%2C%20which%20protects%20our%20planet%20from%20harmful%20solar%20radiation.%20Although%20the%20inner%20core's%20direct%20influence%20on%20the%20magnetic%20field%20is%20not%20fully%20understood%2C%20scientists%20reported%20in%202023%20that%20a%20slower-spinning%20core%20could%20potentially%20impact%20it%20and%20also%20slightly%20shorten%20the%20length%20of%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Vidale%20and%20his%20coauthors%20observed%20seismic%20waves%20produced%20by%20earthquakes%20in%20the%20same%20locations%20at%20different%20times%20for%20this%20study.%20They%20found%20121%20examples%20of%20such%20earthquakes%20occurring%20between%201991%20and%202023%20in%20the%20South%20Sandwich%20Islands%2C%20an%20archipelago%20of%20volcanic%20islands%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20to%20the%20east%20of%20South%20America's%20southernmost%20tip.%20The%20researchers%20also%20looked%20at%20core-penetrating%20shock%20waves%20from%20Soviet%20nuclear%20tests%20conducted%20between%201971%20and%201974.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20revealed%20that%20the%20core%20is%20now%20spinning%20much%20slower%20and%20accelerates%20at%20different%20rates%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20going%20to%20need%20an%20explanation%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Vidale%20said.%20The%20scientists%20feel%20that%20one%20possibility%20could%20be%20metal%20inner%20core%20is%20not%20as%20solid%20as%20expected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20depth%20and%20inaccessibility%20of%20the%20inner%20core%20mean%20that%20uncertainties%20remain.%20Although%2C%20changes%20in%20core%20spin%20can%20be%20tracked%20and%20measured.%20The%20researchers%20highlighted%20that%20when%20the%20core%20spins%20slowly%2C%20the%20mantle%20speeds%20up.%20This%20shift%20makes%20Earth%20move%20faster%2C%20and%20the%20length%20of%20a%20day%20shortens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20that%20effect%20in%20a%20person's%20lifetime%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20imagine%20it%20means%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720323240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-03%2Fearth-mantle_650x400_41488715210.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-confirm-earths-core-has-slowed-dramatically-now-moving-in-reverse-6051284%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20said%20that%20the%20slowing%20down%20could%20change%20the%20length%20of%20one%20day%20on%20the%20Earth%20by%20fractions%20of%20a%20second.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-confirm-earths-core-has-slowed-dramatically-now-moving-in-reverse-6051284%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2